article.headline: Columbia 24, Iona 0
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Craig Hormann threw for 215 yards and a touchdown as Columbia defeated Iona 24-0 Saturday in the first meeting between the schools. Columbia (3-1) managed 298 yards in total offense against the Gaels (1-5), who came into the game leading Division I-AA in total defense. Hormann completed 22 of 37 passes for Columbia, which earned its first shutout since a 24-0 win over Harvard in 1998. Iona's Michael Biehl was 17-of-28 for 155 yards, replacing Gaels' starter Dustin Croick, who missed the game with a leg injury. Hormann threw a 1-yard pass to Austin Knowlin with 11 seconds remaining in the first quarter to cap a 72-yard drive and give the Lions a 7-0 lead. Jon Rocholl kicked a 42-yard field goal on the final play of the first half to extend the lead to 10-0. Columbia converted two turnovers into second-half touchdowns. Darren Schmidt recovered a fumble by Biehl in the Iona end zone in the third quarter after a sack by the Lions' Drew Quinn. Chad Musgrove ran 75 yards after intercepting a pass by Biehl intended for Brian Watts early in the fourth quarter. Iona played without coach Fred Mariani, who was hospitalized after becoming ill during practice Friday. Defensive coordinator Ed Lynett handled the coaching duties.
